		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Ideas</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Above posts regarding CoH&nbsp;are great. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Give us something raid needed that needs more than 1 mage to cast during raids. Example group/ae mana regen similar to paragon but it instantly kills our pet to cast, something along group siphon lines make it a slowish refresh timer. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Another idea is anti summoning spell when cast on target/targets it makes them immune to being summoned for x amount of time. While only situationally useful it would be nice to cast on clerics that are only getting temporary agro from initial heals so the tank can secure his holding agro. This would be really useful.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Reverse CoH, let us summon ourselves to our group member. This would save a lot of time and needless deaths. Even this may not make us actually needed at least no more than 1 mage, but would be an awesome utility.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Give us group elemental forms that can use mounts. This will be a small way to give clerics small extra mana regen, or to give group better resists, or more HP for tanks. While elemental forms are minor upgrades on these things it is still a useful utility. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Give us an aa that allows us to cast rods with faster reusability. Anything that gives more mana regen is a great utility. Take 30 seconds off of the reuse time on them for each level of the aa.&nbsp; IF someone actually uses the rods as fast as they can be used it will improve the rods ie the mages usefulness.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Lastly if none of these utilities are going to be used/considered at the very least upgrade our DPS to be on par with wizards/rogues to justify our lack of defense, be it pet DPS, nuke DPS or both. We fall into the catagory of DPS since we have lack of utilities/healing yet we are NOT a high end DPS class. If raids think/know mages are as needed as wizards are for dps then we will actually be needed again, more than one mage per raid.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>When you think of the things that are needed during a raid to beat the encounters that you made, think of mages, and what role they are filling in the 54 person raids. ATM we have no use and wind up on the wait list because every other class in the raid is more needed than we are. Give us a reason that we ARE needed. So if we are lucky enough to get to participate in a raid we dont feel useless while there like we are now. Give us something that will give our guilds a reason to need mages there, if you dont understand I will make a class list as to why every other class is needed and we are not.</DIV>
