		" 
			>
			<DIV>Hmm, dont have to be to work until later then I thought today.&nbsp; Sooooo,</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As I looked at my list and thought of "Group Utility" I tried to place much of it in the following:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Healing:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Crowd Control:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Tanking:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Damage:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Damage mitigation:&nbsp; IE slows</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Our real drawback IMO is the lack of utility in the areas of Healing, Crowd control or Damage Mitigation.&nbsp; Often I feel we try to offset this with incredible damage we deal out and rightly so if we continue to have zero utility in the other arena's.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>We are the only class with zero crowd control (other then summoned) utility without a pet.&nbsp; IE stuns, snares, roots for ghetto CC or the all powerful enchanter or even Bard Mezzes and in today's game no mitigation = dead group. (Crowd control is effectively damage mitigation for this purpose)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So as an update to my previous post, any changes should involve giving us utility in either the arena's of Crowd control or damage mitigation to make us "group friendly OR a DPS which is so incredible as to make this lack of utilty a non-concern.</DIV>
<DIV>If developers choose the DPS role (because it is an easy "fix") then pets should be able to offtank as mini crowd control for at least 30 seconds without enrage regardless of the zone.&nbsp; This at least makes us a little more desirable because it gives the true CC / damage mitigation classes time to react and get several mobs under control.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As for further ideas.&nbsp; I'm done.&nbsp; Last time I checked I'm not getting paid for this.&nbsp; In fact I'm paying $14 per month and about $30 bucks every few months to continue playing with a diminishing class.&nbsp; This is an issue SoE is being paid to fix and I think it's time they presented THEIR ideas to us for feedback.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Thanks,</DIV>
<DIV>Ninka</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
