		" 
			>
			I do not want more pet toys that are able to be given to other class' pets, because frankly they are far far too close to ours. However if items could be coded to only be used by the Mage's pets that would be amazing. Also I am not a buffer (besides DS), nor a vending machine. Items will not help group utility as they can simply be "vended: out to others before you join the group. It's time to get rid of the "Vending machine" stigma that has been attatched to our class for so long.<br><br>So, as far as utility I suggest a continuation of our debuffs, in the form of conjuring tiny (perhaps elemental themed) monsters (not even an actual entity, but much in the same way Druids and Rangers summon swarms of bees)to carry out a specific task.<br><br>Sparklings- A horde of miniscule fire imps speed towards your target, engulfing it in a swarm of sparks and burns, making it hard to focus. Check: Fire -50, lowers the target's Fire resist and increasing cast time by whatever ammount would work for the level it is implemented. These would stack with other debuffs to add a little extra.<br><br>Frostlings- Tiny ice elementals mob your target, raking icy cold claws down it and chilling its nerves.<br>Check: Cold- 50, lowers resists to Cold and Magic.<br><br>Rockrunners- Diminutive dust mephits pick and pry at the target's armor and attempt to knock weapons from it's hands. Check: Earth is usually assosiated with Disease, but perhaps Magic - 50. Lowers AC and ATK<br><br>Slyphs- Alarmingly fast Slyphs assualt your target, distracting it for a moment as it attempts to swat them away. Check: Magic (no resist mod). With these debuffs aggro will be a problem, so this is our much awaited aggro reducer. Very very fast cast time as if it is too long it will begin to impede our DPS rather than aid it.<br><br>I like the idea of the line (Summoning tiny mephits and such to annoy and harass your opponent), and perhaps some things could use some tweaking, or change. If it is decided we need root/snare/or even a Rune (instead of attacking us the tiny dust beast valiantly sheild master) these could factor in, just tossing out some ideas to add a bit of variety. I'm not saying these are amazing, must institute now ideas, but just what I have off the top of my mind.
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Zarath Stoneshaper- Arch Convoker
