<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Zabren wrote:<BR>
<DIV>I suppose I differ from most folks on this issue. I don't want to buff people or spend endless ours summoning items like a freaking vending machine.&nbsp; As a mage I want to cause massive amounts of damage with my pet and supplement that damage with my nukes.&nbsp; The reason I created my mage way back in the pre-kunark days is because I wanted to control a pet that could go in and put a hurting on my enemies.&nbsp; Unfortunately, due to the way that EQ has evolved I no longer am able to do that.&nbsp; I greatly outdamage my pet&nbsp; on raid type encounters and it shouldn't be that way.&nbsp; I don't want to be a 3rd rate wizard.&nbsp; I'm a MAGE, I want a pet that is respected as a sizable contributer to DPS in a group or raid.&nbsp; If I don't have a pet summoned on a raid, I should be getting tells asking why I don't have one up.&nbsp; I should have a pet that is respected by others enough that I won't get turned down for Vxed trials because the group wants a real pet in the form of an enchanter charmed pet.&nbsp; I should have a pet respected enough that raiding guilds will recruit mages for dps like they do wizards.&nbsp; My utility to groups and raids should be damage.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Zabren</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV>I agree with you a 100%</DIV>
<DIV>The&nbsp;lack of utility the mage class suffer should be made for in damage and&nbsp;yes I want mages to be invited to guilds like wizards do for their damage (even though I consider&nbsp;wizards to have supperior utility).&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This lack of damage should be made up for in damage done by the pet (but if devs think it should be made by improving nukes and making the gap between mage and wizard nukes the same as it was back in kunark I can live with that). Pet damage should pehabs be increase all over but also through pet focus items just like wizard scaling is done by focus items. But to do this the amount of bonus the foci items deliever should be increase significantly and the amount of pet pet foci drops should be increase especially in PoP (you dont see lack of cold focus item compared to pet foci items now do you).</DIV>
<DIV>I too hate to be a vending machine my summons by 90% of the times goes to twinking pets of random ppl that run past me in PoK.</DIV>
<DIV>Back when I made my mage I remember that I feelt it was ok not to have root/snare not to have a damage absorbing shield, not to be able to quadkite for huge amounts of xp, not to have the best nukes, which was the stuff my wizard friends always bragged about, for I had a pet I feelt made up for that. Now that my pet has decreased in dps compared to that what epic made on raid encounts and xp mobs back in the kunark days, now that my pet still is nothing more than a speedbump for most mobs I encounter, now that the DPS difference between wizard and mage nukes have increased compared to kunark&nbsp;(and seems to be increaseing even more with OoW - I know its still in test phase but...), now that I only hear "we need dps - where are our wizards", I have come to the conclussion that I might have picked the wrong class. But I also know I won't be rerolling I spendt to much time with this game as it is if I am going to reroll then let it be in WoW or another game where it makes sence to start all over again.</DIV>	
