		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>Here's what I'd like to see:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<OL>
<LI><STRONG>Summoned Focus&nbsp;Augments </STRONG>- Summoned focus items should get turned into summoned augments with the same effects.&nbsp; Alternatively, give mages some way to bestow focus effects on other players without using a buff slot, maybe via the tribute system somehow.&nbsp; Focus items force people to use an item with otherwise junk stats in order to get the focus effect, and for a lot of players, that just isn't worth it.&nbsp; Not to mention at the high-end, players will have the same or better foci from equipment already.</LI>
<LI><STRONG>Improved Damage Shields </STRONG>-&nbsp;The recent improvements are a start, but they should not be categorized as Done. &nbsp;They're now to the point where they're on par with Druid damage shields, but neither Druid <EM>or </EM>Mage damage shields were very high-demand buffs.&nbsp; Currently, on raids these aren't considered worth wasting a buff slot on -- they just don't do anywhere near enough damage to be worth the trouble, even with a 15 minute duration.&nbsp; Druids already have plenty of worthwhile buffs, but Mages just have this as a targettable buff.&nbsp; It needs to do a lot more damage, or have some other meaningful effect (like shielding, or improved parry, etc), or it should just get removed from our spell&nbsp;lineup.</LI>
<LI><STRONG>Cross-zone Call of the Hero </STRONG>-&nbsp;Maybe this should be an AA, but we should get the ability to cast this across zonelines on people who are not in our group.&nbsp; I'm picturing something where gaining this AA provides the mage with a new /coth command.&nbsp; The mage simply types /coth and a confirmation dialog box appears on the target player's screen.&nbsp; If they accept, they are transported to the mage's location.&nbsp; This would make mages a very convenient class for adding people to your raid/group.&nbsp; Should have a recast time of &lt; 2 minutes (ideally, recast would be 10-15 seconds, 1.5 hours would be worthless).</LI>
<LI><STRONG>Built-in Modrod Timer</STRONG> - Just a message that shows up in yellow saying "Your Mystical Transvergence has worn off." or some other message that lets you know your modrod timer has expired.&nbsp; Help people make better use of some utility we already have.</LI>
<LI><STRONG>Damage&nbsp;Focus Ward AA</STRONG> - Lots of classes got one of these with GoD, I'd like to see one for us too.&nbsp; Make it something like 2%/5%/10% for 4/8/12 AA.&nbsp; Would be good both for groups (without a Bard), and on raids where there usually aren't enough Bards to go around to cover everyone.</LI></OL>
<P>Really, I'd like to see an answer on what our defined role is, and where we're supposed to be ranked in terms of DPS before we go talking about enhancing utility.&nbsp; I'd trade all of the above just to see mages get back to being one of the top damage-dealing classes.</P>
<P>-Olwyn</P>	
		</td></tr>
