<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=magicianbalance&message.id=1590#M1590">43</a> of 83
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 359 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Better Utility in Groups and Raids</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>Lets face it. The magician needs more utility to be a viable entity in groups and raids.&nbsp; Whether it be to up our DPS value or to give us more of a functional buff or debuff type role we need this so that we arent always the last ones to get picked. When my guild was going through PoTime for the first time and picking groups for the Phase 1 trials, and doing Tipt and Vxed in GoD the mages were left on the sidelines till the end for the most part because of the lack of functionality.&nbsp; </DIV></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>From what Ive read some people want the things that mages already do better, and then some want the devs to reinvent the wheel it seems. I whole heartedly believe with the direction this game is going and has been going over the past few expansions it may be time for a little of both.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>CotH -- Increase the zones that it works in. I understand the need for it not to be used in some zones because of content.&nbsp; But we should be atleast able to CoTH to a point in every zone that Summon Corpse works in. You did it in PoFire.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Group Spell Defense -- A line of spells that takes some of the damage away from those nasty AE's, procs, and DD's&nbsp;that NPC's have now.&nbsp; And dont make it like Reflect. If its only for PC spells it is worthless. Make it a time duration not a set amount of damage before it disipates. Like 15 - 40% of damage negation. I know wizzies and enchanters have runes and spellshields to cast on&nbsp;people. This line would make it unigue because it is groupable, and it wouldnt go away after 1 AE, proc, or DD went off. This would also make the MGB AA not so worthless!!!</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Debuff -- Malosinia is too easily resisted. We shouldnt have to depend on Shamans to cast Malo first. In most cases slow needs to be landed immediately on raids with the HPs mobs can take off these days.&nbsp; Change the resist mod to this spell.&nbsp; Nothing angers me more to click my Veil of Lost Hopes repeatedly to never have it land on so many tries.&nbsp; Not to mention the mana wasted before I got the mask.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Magician DPS -- Anyway you look at it being either spell damage or pet damage we are lacking. Seeing druids crit for almost what I do, and then seeing what a wizard can do with White Fire boggles my mind.&nbsp; Mage DPS needs to be adjusted greatly.&nbsp; However the devs decide to do it will be fine with me lets just get it done.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Give the magician something along the lines of Levant like necros.&nbsp; An AA will do fine.&nbsp; That way more than one mage will be needed on a raid and we can keep the CoTH chain going ourselves not having to depend on the druid or wizard for help.&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Magician nukes are too easily resisted or they land for half the damage or less too often. Lessen the resist mod to our spells so maybe that would up our&nbsp;DPS.&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
