		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>

<DIV>As for further ideas.&nbsp; I'm done.&nbsp; Last time I checked I'm not getting paid for this.&nbsp; In fact I'm paying $14 per month and about $30 bucks every few months to continue playing with a diminishing class.&nbsp; This is an issue SoE is being paid to fix and I think it's time they presented THEIR ideas to us for feedback.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Thanks,</DIV>
<DIV>Ninka<BR>
<HR>
</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Here here!&nbsp; Let's hear SoE's ideas.&nbsp; We can help eliminate the ones that won't really be beneficial before they spend a bunch of time implementing them and then tell us we are "done" because our DS lasts a little longer.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>Some reactions to other comments.</P>
<P>Mage pets are generally not welcome in raids (at any level of the game)&nbsp;due to control issues.&nbsp; That&nbsp;eliminates (very roughly) 50% of our damage, because raid leaders too often&nbsp;don't allow pets on general principles.&nbsp; If magicians got some new tools for controlling pets (see my previous post), raid leaders will see that change and perhaps be more willing to welcome magicians and their pets.&nbsp; Someone said that we should run around and manually position our pets.&nbsp; Some of that does happen, but too often the geometry and/or tactical situation doesn't allow for it.&nbsp; Worse, when I'm running around I'm not casting DD.</P>
<P>Another idea for pet control (less button pushing, more "action" for us) is to have the ability to take Eye of Zomm style control of our melee&nbsp;pet for 30 seconds or so to position him.&nbsp; Note that you can still nuke while moving an eye...</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>There were some folks that made the comment that many of the suggestions being made only help one magician get into a raid.&nbsp; I would counter that raids are not what the average player does every day, and these ideas would increase our utility and desirability in groups, so they are still valuable ideas.&nbsp; </P>
<P>Plus, wouldn't it still be an improvement if raids refused to start until at least one&nbsp;magician could be found?&nbsp;&nbsp; For a very very&nbsp;limited number of encounters, that is already true due to CoH.&nbsp; If CoH worked in more places, then mages would be needed more often (well, depending on what places they choose.&nbsp; The "same as&nbsp; where necro corpse summon works" seems like a very good basis).&nbsp; Before they nerfed pet resists, it was true of a few other encounters.&nbsp; They should rethink that change and bring back pets with type-specific immunities.&nbsp; Those nasty AoE's that cream our pets - make it so if you are using the right pet, he resists it, rather than (or in addition to)&nbsp;relying on Calliav.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>07-12-2004</span> <span class=time_text>12:42 PM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_rating_cell" valign=bottom nowrap 
			
			>
			
